223
00:22:02,976 --> 00:22:05,185
——莫妮卡。-是的,请莫妮卡。
-Not Monika. -Yeah, Monika, please.

224
00:22:05,324 --> 00:22:07,222
不，我见过太多了。
Nah, seen it too often.

225
00:22:07,360 --> 00:22:09,258
——[托尼]排演之后?范妮和亚历山大?
-[Tony] After the Rehearsal? -Fanny and Alexander?

226
00:22:09,397 --> 00:22:11,847
同样的事情。这句话我已经背下来了。
Same thing. I know that one by heart.

227
00:22:11,985 --> 00:22:13,228
第七封印。
The Seventh Seal.

228
00:22:13,366 --> 00:22:15,368
不，我受不了那个。
No, I can't stand that one.

229
00:22:15,506 --> 00:22:18,095
但这是他最著名的作品，我还没看过。
But it's his most famous one, and I haven't seen it.

230
00:22:18,233 --> 00:22:20,546
-狼的时刻?-不，就是那个
-Hour of the Wolf? -No, that's the one

231
00:22:20,684 --> 00:22:22,548
一个孩子的头被石头砸到。
where a child's head gets bashed against a boulder.

232
00:22:22,686 --> 00:22:24,135
正确的。
Right.

233
00:22:24,273 --> 00:22:25,274
不，如果我们看不到第七封印，
No, if we don't see Seventh Seal,

234
00:22:25,413 --> 00:22:26,759
那至少是一个不错的。
then at least a nice one.

235
00:22:26,897 --> 00:22:28,208
没有这样的东西。
There's no such thing.

236
00:22:29,382 --> 00:22:30,866
然后我们下载一部电影。
Then we download a film.

237
00:22:31,004 --> 00:22:32,247
你想看珠穆朗玛峰。这是更容易。
You wanted to see Everest. It's easier.

238
00:22:32,385 --> 00:22:34,456
源!-我知道。
-Source! -I know.

239
00:22:34,594 --> 00:22:36,182
萨拉邦德舞。
Saraband.

240
00:22:36,320 --> 00:22:37,701
是的,萨拉邦德舞。
Yeah, Saraband.

241
00:22:37,839 --> 00:22:39,910
-我没有那个。-哦,操。
-I don't have that one. -Oh, fuck.

242
00:22:40,048 --> 00:22:42,913
否则我就有35毫米的照片了。我们之前展示过。
Or else I have a 35mm print. We showed it earlier.

243
00:22:43,051 --> 00:22:44,708
它明天就要回斯德哥尔摩了。
It's going back to Stockholm tomorrow.

244
00:22:44,846 --> 00:22:47,400
什么电影?哭泣和低语。
-What film? -Cries and Whispers.

245
00:22:47,538 --> 00:22:50,783
-你想要一个漂亮的伯格曼。嗯。
-You wanted a nice Bergman. -Hmm.

246
00:22:50,921 --> 00:22:52,888
好吧，你想坐哪儿都行，
Alright, you can sit anywhere you want,

247
00:22:53,026 --> 00:22:54,787
但不是在第一排的那个座位上。
but not in that seat on the first row.

248
00:22:54,925 --> 00:22:57,617
它必须空着，因为这是伯格曼的。
It has to stay empty because it's Bergman's.

249
00:22:59,032 --> 00:23:00,379
-对吗?-谢谢。
-Right? -Thanks.

250
00:23:00,517 --> 00:23:02,519
(风扇转动)
[fans whirring]

251
00:23:19,605 --> 00:23:21,434
(投影仪转动)
[projector whirring]

252
00:23:25,542 --> 00:23:27,267
(钟声间歇性地)
[bells toll intermittently]

253
00:23:31,927 --> 00:23:34,309
(深哭泣)
[deep sobbing]

254
00:23:38,934 --> 00:23:40,971
(继续哭泣)
[sobbing continues]

255
00:23:41,109 --> 00:23:43,905
[女子说外语]
[woman speaks in foreign language]

256
00:23:51,430 --> 00:23:54,294
[电影中忧郁的音乐]
[melancholy music in film]

257
00:23:57,815 --> 00:24:00,197
[音乐继续时无音频]
[no audio while music continues]

258
00:24:23,289 --> 00:24:26,741
就像一部没有精神宣泄的恐怖电影。
It's a like a horror movie without catharsis.

259
00:24:26,879 --> 00:24:28,605
你的意思是?
[Tony] Your point being?

260
00:24:28,743 --> 00:24:32,194
通常当你看完恐怖片后
Well, usually when you come out of a horror movie,

261
00:24:33,023 --> 00:24:34,852
你觉得放心
you feel reassured

262
00:24:34,990 --> 00:24:36,958
因为你知道你刚才看到的不会发生在你身上。
because you know what you just saw can't happen to you.

263
00:24:37,096 --> 00:24:39,029
不是用哭泣和低语。
Not with Cries and Whispers.

264
00:24:39,167 --> 00:24:42,135
孤独，痛苦，死亡的恐惧。
The solitude, the agony, the horror of dying.

265
00:24:42,273 --> 00:24:43,516
事情就是这样。
It's the way things are.

266
00:24:43,654 --> 00:24:45,725
不,它不是。这是一个梦。
No, it's not. It's a dream.

267
00:24:45,863 --> 00:24:48,072
或者更像是一场噩梦。
Or more like a fucking nightmare.

268
00:24:48,210 --> 00:24:50,972
我只希望他的生活比他的电影更有趣。
I just hope he had more fun in his life than in his movies.

269
00:24:51,110 --> 00:24:52,870
我也是。
Me too.

270
00:24:55,839 --> 00:24:58,117
为什么他的角色总是那么糟糕?
Why are his characters always so awful?

271
00:24:58,255 --> 00:25:01,085
为什么他从来没有表现出任何温柔或轻松?
Why doesn't he ever show any tenderness or lightness?

272
00:25:01,223 --> 00:25:03,605
范妮和亚历山大有很多。
There's loads in Fanny and Alexander.

273
00:25:03,743 --> 00:25:05,262
没错，但为时已晚。
True, but that came late.

274
00:25:05,400 --> 00:25:06,919
是啊，不过晚了也挺好的，对吧?
Yeah, but it's good that it came late, right?

275
00:25:07,057 --> 00:25:08,748
他对变轻不感兴趣。
He wasn't interested in being light.

276
00:25:08,886 --> 00:25:11,544
他很黑暗，他想探索这一点。
He--he was dark, and he wanted to explore that.

277
00:25:11,682 --> 00:25:12,821
这对他来说很有趣。
It was fun for him.

278
00:25:14,029 --> 00:25:15,583
为什么他一次也没有
Why didn't he ever once

279
00:25:15,721 --> 00:25:17,032
想探索——
want to explore--

280
00:25:17,170 --> 00:25:19,207
幸福吗?-是的,幸福!
-Happiness? -Yeah, happiness!

281
00:25:19,345 --> 00:25:21,796
我是说，看看这地方。
I mean, look at this place.

282
00:25:21,934 --> 00:25:25,075
他的房子，小岛，美丽的风景。
His houses, the island, beautiful landscapes.

283
00:25:25,213 --> 00:25:28,423
一切都没有他电影里那么残酷。
Everything is less harsh than in his movies.

284
00:25:28,561 --> 00:25:30,598
那就他妈一月再来这里试试。
Then try this place in fucking January.

285
00:25:30,736 --> 00:25:32,392
不了,谢谢。
No, thank you.

286
00:25:37,018 --> 00:25:38,744
有什么事吗?
What's the matter?

287
00:25:40,228 --> 00:25:42,713
电影可以是非常悲伤的，
Movies can be terribly sad,

288
00:25:42,851 --> 00:25:44,991
强硬,暴力,
tough, violent,

289
00:25:45,129 --> 00:25:47,304
但最终，它们对你有好处。
but in the end, they do you good.

290
00:25:47,442 --> 00:25:49,755
他不?-不。
-His don't? -No.

291
00:25:49,893 --> 00:25:51,101
只是伤害我。
Just hurt me.

292
00:25:51,239 --> 00:25:52,827
那你为什么还要看?
Then why do you watch them then?

293
00:25:52,965 --> 00:25:54,932
因为我爱他们。
Because I love them.

294
00:25:55,070 --> 00:25:58,142
我只是不知道为什么，就这样。
I just don't know why, that's all.

295
00:26:10,948 --> 00:26:12,743
(喘气)
[panting]

296
00:26:20,579 --> 00:26:21,752
(人)吉娜!
[man] Gina!

297
00:26:22,995 --> 00:26:24,583
(喘息)谢谢!
[gasps] Please!

298
00:26:24,721 --> 00:26:26,895
有人在这里吗?
Anybody in here?

299
00:26:27,931 --> 00:26:29,346
拜托!
Please!

300
00:26:29,484 --> 00:26:31,417
求求你，我有危险，求求你!
Please, I'm in danger, please!

301
00:26:31,555 --> 00:26:33,350
有人!
Someone!

302
00:26:39,321 --> 00:26:40,806
吉娜!
Gina!

303
00:26:54,509 --> 00:26:56,925
(关于砾石)脚步
[footsteps on gravel]

304
00:27:01,274 --> 00:27:02,379
(叹息)
[groans]

305
00:27:14,633 --> 00:27:16,462
(聊天)
[chatter]

306
00:27:18,015 --> 00:27:20,362
几乎结束了。-[托尼]还好吗?
-Almost over. -[Tony] How's it doing?

307
00:27:20,500 --> 00:27:22,571
你再也不看电影了吗?
Don't you ever watch your movies again?

308
00:27:22,710 --> 00:27:25,436
-不。我讨厌它。-伯格曼曾经对他说，地狱，
-No. I hate it. -Bergman used to say that Hell, to him,

309
00:27:25,574 --> 00:27:26,990
如果他要看自己的电影，他会怎么想
would be if he had to watch his own movies

310
00:27:27,128 --> 00:27:29,268
一遍又一遍。我同意。
-over and over again. -I agree.

311
00:27:29,406 --> 00:27:30,579
演职员表刚刚开始，
The credits just started,

312
00:27:30,718 --> 00:27:32,167
-所以我们往里面走。-好的。
-so we move head inside. -Okay.

313
00:27:32,305 --> 00:27:35,550
(低沉的掌声)
[muffled applause]

314
00:27:38,208 --> 00:27:40,313
(欢呼声和功能)
[cheers and whistles]

315
00:27:44,663 --> 00:27:47,907
让我们再次欢迎安东尼·桑德斯。
[Berit] And please welcome again Anthony Sanders.

316
00:27:51,877 --> 00:27:53,361
[托尼]在我的一生中，
[Tony] All of my life,

317
00:27:53,499 --> 00:27:55,915
我觉得我就像在走钢丝，
I felt like I was, um, on a tightrope,

318
00:27:56,053 --> 00:27:59,401
你知道，我一直在平衡，
you know, I was kind of balancing,

319
00:27:59,539 --> 00:28:01,610
如果我掉下来，如果我掉下来，我就
and, uh, if I fell-- if I fell off, I just--

320
00:28:01,749 --> 00:28:04,130
我就会迷失，完全消失。
I'd be lost, I'd be completely gone.

321
00:28:04,268 --> 00:28:07,858
所以，作为一个电影制作人，我只觉得，嗯…
And so, as a filmmaker, only really felt, um...

322
00:28:07,996 --> 00:28:09,791
(如今)
[stammers]

323
00:28:09,929 --> 00:28:12,345
．．.安全,我想,
...secure, I suppose,

324
00:28:12,483 --> 00:28:13,795
,和舒适
and--and comfortable

325
00:28:13,933 --> 00:28:15,763
如果故事的中心人物
if the central character of the story

326
00:28:15,901 --> 00:28:19,249
我当时说她是女性。
I was telling at that particular time was, um, female.

327
00:28:19,387 --> 00:28:23,425
那些女人，她们让你接触到现实
The women, they keep you in touch with reality and--

328
00:28:23,563 --> 00:28:26,256
但与此同时，他们也是
But at the same time, they are the ones who

329
00:28:26,394 --> 00:28:27,947
把你拉进小说里。
pull you into fiction.

330
00:28:28,085 --> 00:28:30,087
你的大部分电影都是由他们主导的。
They drive the action in most of your films.

331
00:28:30,225 --> 00:28:31,433
[托尼]是的，女人喜欢。
[Tony] The women do, yeah.

332
00:29:05,329 --> 00:29:07,815
——[人]嘿。-你好。
-[man] Hey. -Hello.

333
00:29:07,953 --> 00:29:10,300
(安静的聊天)
[quiet chatter]

334
00:29:34,324 --> 00:29:36,705
能把这些给我吗?
Hey, uh, can I get these?

335
00:29:36,844 --> 00:29:37,948
[人]是的,当然。
[man] Yeah, sure.

336
00:29:38,086 --> 00:29:39,950
请800克朗。
800 crowns please.

337
00:30:13,639 --> 00:30:15,814
你输了。
You're lost.

338
00:30:15,952 --> 00:30:17,539
在那里。
Over there.

339
00:30:17,677 --> 00:30:18,678
你必须绕过去。
You have to go around.

340
00:30:18,817 --> 00:30:20,819
噢,谢谢你。
Oh, thank you.

341
00:30:25,375 --> 00:30:27,204
比比眼镜里的东西怎么样了?
How are things through Bibi's glasses?

342
00:30:27,342 --> 00:30:28,896
——好。——Hampus。
-Much better. --Hampus.

343
00:30:29,034 --> 00:30:30,932
屁股的。-你做住院医生?
-Chris. -You do the residency?

344
00:30:31,070 --> 00:30:33,693
哦,是的。和我的朋友安东尼·桑德斯。
Oh, yeah. Well, with my friend, Anthony Sanders.

345
00:30:33,832 --> 00:30:35,523
——你呢?加了。
-And you? -Me too.

346
00:30:35,661 --> 00:30:38,181
我正在制作我的毕业短片。
I'm working on my short graduation film here.

347
00:30:38,319 --> 00:30:41,046
但我了解法罗。我的祖父母来自这里。
But I know Faro. My grandparents are from here.

348
00:30:55,750 --> 00:30:58,304
我本应该待到八月中旬的，
I was supposed to stay until mid-August,

349
00:30:58,442 --> 00:31:01,238
但我明天要去看我爷爷。
but I'm leaving tomorrow to see my grandfather.

350
00:31:01,376 --> 00:31:02,930
他的死亡。
He's dying.

351
00:31:03,068 --> 00:31:04,379
哦,我很抱歉。
Oh, I'm sorry.

352
00:31:04,517 --> 00:31:06,105
哦,他太老了。
Oh, he's old.

353
00:31:06,243 --> 00:31:08,418
我想看看伯格曼的坟墓。
I'd like to see Bergman's grave.

354
00:31:08,556 --> 00:31:11,524
-你知道在哪儿吗?当然,来吧。
-Do you know where it is? -Sure, come on.

355
00:31:13,147 --> 00:31:15,149
我和我女朋友在哥德堡看了你最后一部电影。
I saw your last film at Goteborg with my girlfriend.

356
00:31:15,287 --> 00:31:17,979
-哦。除了我们，剧院里空无一人。
-Oh. -Besides us, the theater was empty.

357
00:31:18,117 --> 00:31:19,808
后来我们吵了一架，
Then we got in a fight afterwards,

358
00:31:19,947 --> 00:31:22,121
因为我喜欢，她不喜欢。她讨厌它。
because I liked it and she didn't. She hated it.

359
00:31:22,259 --> 00:31:24,468
-我们后来分手了。有关这部电影吗?
-We broke up afterwards. -Over the movie?

360
00:31:24,606 --> 00:31:26,505
不，不是看电影的时候。
No, not over the movie.

361
00:31:26,643 --> 00:31:28,887
[树叶在风中沙沙作响]
[leaves rustling in the wind]

362
00:32:02,506 --> 00:32:04,025
伯格曼导演了他自己的死亡。
Bergman directed his own death.

363
00:32:04,163 --> 00:32:06,338
他提前决定了一切:
He decided everything in advance:

364
00:32:06,476 --> 00:32:08,823
那个地方，棺材的木头，还有他会穿什么。
the spot, the wood of the coffin, and what he'd wear.

365
00:32:08,961 --> 00:32:10,790
基金会的海达说
Hedda from the Foundation said

366
00:32:10,929 --> 00:32:13,276
在他妻子死后
that after his wife died,

367
00:32:13,414 --> 00:32:15,795
他开始相信有来世。
he started believing in an afterlife.

368
00:32:15,934 --> 00:32:17,556
他是一位牧师的儿子。
He was the son of a minister.

369
00:32:17,694 --> 00:32:19,489
所以，信仰的问题一直伴随着他。
So, the question of faith always followed him.

370
00:32:19,627 --> 00:32:22,664
[说外语]
[speaks in foreign language]

371
00:32:22,802 --> 00:32:24,528
“哦，上帝，你为什么抛弃我?”
[translates in English] "Oh, God, why have you abandoned me?"

372
00:32:24,666 --> 00:32:27,600
但现在瑞典没人真正关心这个了。
But nobody in Sweden really cares now.

373
00:32:29,671 --> 00:32:31,466
哦,他妈的!
Oh, fuck!

374
00:32:31,604 --> 00:32:34,193
我要去伯格曼动物园。
I'm supposed to do the Bergman Safari.

375
00:32:34,331 --> 00:32:36,161
Bergman Safari，你可以跳过这个。
Bergman Safari, you can skip that.

376
00:32:36,299 --> 00:32:38,818
是的，是给托尼的。他不想一个人去。
Yeah, it's for Tony. He didn't want to do it alone.

377
00:32:38,957 --> 00:32:40,613
如果你想看伯格曼的景点，
If you want to see the Bergman spots,

378
00:32:40,751 --> 00:32:41,994
我可以给你看。
I can show them to you.

379
00:32:42,132 --> 00:32:43,513
我还可以给你看其他的。
I can also show you others.

380
00:32:43,651 --> 00:32:45,032
这些是你在Safari上看不到的。
Ones you'd never see on the Safari.

381
00:32:45,170 --> 00:32:46,481
-是吗?-是的。
-Yeah? -Yeah.

382
00:32:46,619 --> 00:32:48,414
——是难以置信的。-哦,谢谢。
-It was fabulous. -Oh, thank you.

383
00:32:48,552 --> 00:32:51,141
对不起，能给我签个名吗?-是的,当然。
-Sorry, can I have an autograph? -Yeah, absolutely.

384
00:32:51,279 --> 00:32:54,144
(聊天)
[chatter]

385
00:32:54,282 --> 00:32:56,112
你是在这儿。-非常感谢。
-Here you are. -Thank you so very much.

386
00:32:56,250 --> 00:32:58,424
这是迷人的。我钦佩你所做的一切。
It was fascinating. I admire everything you do.

387
00:32:58,562 --> 00:33:01,910
-哦,谢谢。我能照张相吗?
-Oh, thank you. -Can I have a photo please?

388
00:33:03,567 --> 00:33:04,913
-我就是喜欢你的工作。-谢谢。
-I just love your work. -Thank you.

389
00:33:05,052 --> 00:33:06,432
小。-非常感谢。
-Keep going. -Thank you very much.

390
00:33:06,570 --> 00:33:08,089
能给我签个名吗?
Can I please have your autograph?

391
00:33:08,227 --> 00:33:09,918
你是我最喜欢的导演。
Your my favorite director.

392
00:33:10,057 --> 00:33:12,024
你就是我开始学电影的原因。
You're the reason why I started studying cinema.

393
00:33:12,162 --> 00:33:14,268
-谢谢。-很高兴认识你。
-Thank you. -Nice to have met you.

394
00:33:14,406 --> 00:33:16,063
好吧。
Okay.

395
00:33:19,445 --> 00:33:22,000
我有一些苹果酒。这是当地的苹果酒。它是美味的。
[Hampus] I have some cider. It's local cider. It's delicious.

396
00:33:22,138 --> 00:33:23,760
在后面。你能打开吗?
It's in the back. Can you open it?

397
00:33:23,898 --> 00:33:25,762
确定。
Sure.

398
00:33:36,600 --> 00:33:38,395
我们要去哪里?
Where are we going?

399
00:33:40,018 --> 00:33:41,950
我想从《乌拉豪》开始。
I was thinking Ullahau to start.

400
00:33:42,089 --> 00:33:43,193
(克里斯)Ullahau吗?
[Chris] Ullahau?

401
00:33:47,508 --> 00:33:49,165
你好,每个人。
Hello, everyone.

402
00:33:49,303 --> 00:33:51,581
我想我们都到齐了，我们可以走了!
I think that we're all here, so we can get going!

403
00:33:51,719 --> 00:33:54,032
我叫费利西亚，很高兴做你的导游
My name is Felicia, and I'm happy to be your guide

404
00:33:54,170 --> 00:33:55,895
参加一年一度的伯格曼野生动物园
for the annual Bergman Safari.

405
00:33:56,034 --> 00:33:58,967
我的两位同事，薇薇安和马肯，
My two colleagues, Vivianne and Majken,

406
00:33:59,106 --> 00:34:00,314
会帮我的
are going to help me out.

407
00:34:00,452 --> 00:34:02,074
今天天气很好，阳光灿烂，
It is a nice, sunny day,

408
00:34:02,212 --> 00:34:03,903
这是一个很好的优点。
which is a great plus.

409
00:34:04,042 --> 00:34:06,665
对于那些在iphone上下载了应用程序的人，
For those of you who downloaded the app on your iPhones,

410
00:34:06,803 --> 00:34:09,116
现在是时候开始了。
now is the time to start it.

411
00:34:09,254 --> 00:34:11,808
有了它，你就可以跟踪我们的旅程了
With it, you'll be able to follow our journey

412
00:34:11,946 --> 00:34:13,257
在法罗的地图上
on the map of Faro.

413
00:34:13,396 --> 00:34:15,570
现在，如果你们都上车。
Now, if you all come onto the bus.

414
00:34:15,708 --> 00:34:18,746
我之前没介绍你，弗朗西斯科·莫利纳，安东尼·桑德斯。
I didn't introduce you earlier, Francisco Molina, Anthony Sanders.

415
00:34:18,884 --> 00:34:20,472
-你好。快乐。
-How do you do. -Pleasure.

416
00:34:20,610 --> 00:34:22,474
弗朗西斯科在巴塞罗那大学任教。
Francisco teaches at University of Barcelona.

417
00:34:22,612 --> 00:34:25,235
他是昨晚伯格曼测验的当之无愧的冠军。
And he was the hands-down winner of last night's Bergman Quiz.

418
00:34:25,373 --> 00:34:26,822
-哇。-是的。
-Wow. -Yeah.

419
00:34:26,960 --> 00:34:28,963
我们应当?-是的。
-Shall we? -Yeah.

420
00:34:29,101 --> 00:34:31,379
(聊天)
[chatter]

421
00:34:38,041 --> 00:34:40,594
(汽车引擎启动)
[bus engine starts]

422
00:34:43,909 --> 00:34:46,463
[视频中女子说外语]
[woman in video speaks foreign language]

423
00:34:48,085 --> 00:34:50,329
(安静的聊天)
[quiet chatter]

424
00:34:52,020 --> 00:34:53,781
伯格曼不喜欢那部电影。
You know, Bergman didn't like that movie.

425
00:34:53,918 --> 00:34:55,783
对，所以他们才去了意大利。
Yeah, that's why they went to Italy.

426
00:34:55,920 --> 00:34:58,130
是的。里面有所有的东西
Yeah. it's got all the stuff about

427
00:34:58,268 --> 00:35:00,546
他的个人生活，他的婚姻
his personal life, his marriages--

428
00:35:00,684 --> 00:35:02,479
我们到达了伯格曼拍摄《黑色玻璃》的地方，
We're arriving at the spot where Bergman shot Through a Glass Darkly,

429
00:35:02,617 --> 00:35:04,895
这部电影让他发现了法罗。
the film which allowed him to discover Faro.

430
00:35:05,033 --> 00:35:08,140
起初，伯格曼不想在瑞典拍摄。
At first, Bergman didn't want to shoot it in Sweden.

431
00:35:08,278 --> 00:35:09,969
他想去奥克尼群岛
He wanted to go to the Orkney Islands

432
00:35:10,108 --> 00:35:12,006
在苏格兰海岸附近。
off the Scottish coast.

433
00:35:12,144 --> 00:35:14,042
但生产商认为那太贵了。
But the producers thought that that would be far too expensive.

434
00:35:14,181 --> 00:35:17,184
所以，他们试图说服他改在瑞典拍摄。
So, they tried to persuade him to film it in Sweden instead.

435
00:35:48,974 --> 00:35:51,839
这个地方是1700年左右建成的。
This place came to be around 1700.

436
00:35:51,977 --> 00:35:53,772
人们开始砍伐树木，
People started cutting down the trees,

437
00:35:53,910 --> 00:35:55,877
沙子会从北方吹来，
and the sand would blow in from the north,

438
00:35:56,015 --> 00:35:58,535
在空地上形成了这些沙丘
creating these dunes in the clearings.

439
00:35:58,673 --> 00:36:00,744
Ullahau的意思是“翻滚的沙丘”，
Ullahau means "the rolling dunes",

440
00:36:00,882 --> 00:36:03,816
因为人们认为这意味着审判日的到来。
because people thought this meant judgment day was coming.

441
00:36:03,954 --> 00:36:05,335
他们常说…
And they used to say...

442
00:36:05,473 --> 00:36:07,648
(讲瑞典语)
[speaks Swedish]

443
00:36:10,409 --> 00:36:13,757
也就是说，当乌拉豪山和沙丘相遇时，
which means that when Ullahau and sand high meet,

444
00:36:13,895 --> 00:36:16,104
审判日临近了。
judgment day is near.

445
00:36:16,243 --> 00:36:18,866
然后一个人种了许多新树，
And then a man planted many new trees,

446
00:36:19,004 --> 00:36:21,351
阻止更多的沙子进来。
stopping more sand from coming in.

447
00:36:21,489 --> 00:36:25,493
但是原本就在这里的沙丘却保留了下来。
But the dunes that were already here, they remained.

448
00:36:39,887 --> 00:36:42,096
这让我想去海滩。
This makes me want to go to the beach.

449
00:36:42,234 --> 00:36:45,306
——没有问题。-美丽的沙滩。
-It's no problem. -A nice sandy beach.

450
00:36:45,444 --> 00:36:48,896
有两个海滩，北海滩和南海滩。
There is two of them, the north beach and the south beach.

451
00:36:49,034 --> 00:36:51,899
南海滩很大，海浪很大。
The south beach is large, with big waves.

452
00:36:52,037 --> 00:36:53,832
它更适宜游览的。
It's more touristy.

453
00:36:53,970 --> 00:36:57,801
北方没有游客，没有风，水很清澈，
The north has no tourists, no wind, the water is clear,

454
00:36:57,939 --> 00:37:00,735
-但有很多水母。-不。
-but lots of jellyfish. -No way.

455
00:37:00,873 --> 00:37:02,979
是的，但他们是无害的。
Yeah, but they're harmless.

456
00:37:03,117 --> 00:37:05,671
南方也有一些是毒刺。
And the south does have a few which are stingers.

457
00:37:05,809 --> 00:37:07,466
多,更糟。
Much, much worse.

458
00:37:07,604 --> 00:37:09,951
(聊天)
[chatter]

459
00:37:13,334 --> 00:37:16,751
电影里的房子就在这里。
So, the house in the film was here.

460
00:37:16,889 --> 00:37:20,099
实际上，他们只建造了立面和内部
Actually, they only built the facade and the interiors

461
00:37:20,238 --> 00:37:23,137
大部分是在摄影棚拍摄的。-[男人]房子怎么了?
-were mostly shot in studio. -[man] What happened to the house?

462
00:37:23,275 --> 00:37:27,486
嗯，拍完之后他们不得不把它拆掉。
[Felicia] Well, they had to tear it down after the shoot.

463
00:37:27,624 --> 00:37:29,488
伯格曼正在寻找一个小花园
Bergman was looking for a small garden

464
00:37:29,626 --> 00:37:32,250
有老树，这也是他选择这里的原因之一。
with old trees, and that's part of why he picked this spot.

465
00:37:32,388 --> 00:37:34,217
树还在这里，
The trees are still here,

466
00:37:34,355 --> 00:37:36,806
你还可以看到他们拆掉墙的地方。
and you can also see where they took down the wall.

467
00:37:36,944 --> 00:37:41,466
在这里你可以看到墙被替换了。
Here you can see that the wall has been replaced.

468
00:37:41,604 --> 00:37:46,056
一直到…在这里。
All the way to, uh... here.

469
00:37:46,194 --> 00:37:49,094
所以，石头是不同的。这些是他们用过的
So, the stones are different. These are the ones they used

470
00:37:49,232 --> 00:37:50,682
当他们重建长城的时候。
when they rebuilt the wall.

471
00:37:50,820 --> 00:37:53,271
如果你看这里，
And, if you look over here,

472
00:37:55,376 --> 00:37:58,517
你可以看到曾经建过防波堤的地方。
you can see where the jetty once was built.

473
00:37:58,655 --> 00:38:02,659
这就像是防波堤的地基。
So, that was like the foundation of the jetty.

474
00:38:02,797 --> 00:38:06,836
这棵树也在电影里，
And, uh, this tree is actually also in the movie,

475
00:38:06,974 --> 00:38:08,838
但那时它真的很小。
but it was really small then.

476
00:38:08,976 --> 00:38:10,460
所以，它增长了很多
So, it has grown a lot

477
00:38:10,598 --> 00:38:14,015
自从这部电影60年前拍摄以来。
since the film was made about 60 years ago.

478
00:38:14,153 --> 00:38:18,054
伯格曼到达法罗时，发生了一些事情。
When Bergman arrived in Faro, something happened.

479
00:38:18,192 --> 00:38:20,574
这是一见钟情。
It was love at first sight.

480
00:38:20,712 --> 00:38:23,231
伯格曼被这个岛的美丽弄得眼花缭乱。
Bergman was dazzled by the island's beauty.

481
00:38:23,370 --> 00:38:26,925
仿佛他找到了属于自己的风景，
It was as if he had found his own landscape,

482
00:38:27,063 --> 00:38:30,031
一个已经存在于他体内的东西。
one that already existed inside of him.

483
00:38:31,654 --> 00:38:34,519
(温柔的音乐)
[gentle music]

484
00:38:52,847 --> 00:38:55,402
(聊天)
[chatter]

485
00:38:55,540 --> 00:38:58,543
在拍摄《Persona》之前，褒曼曾住院治疗，
Before making Persona, Bergman had been hospitalized,

486
00:38:58,681 --> 00:39:01,200
身心俱疲。
suffering both mental and physical exhaustion.

487
00:39:01,339 --> 00:39:04,894
但在《Persona》之后，他还是一如既往的快乐。
But after Persona, he was as happy as ever.

488
00:39:05,032 --> 00:39:08,898
人物角色体现了这种转变和充实。
Persona incarnates this transition and this fullness.

489
00:39:09,036 --> 00:39:10,865
伯格曼从未忘记它。
Bergman never forgot it.

490
00:39:11,003 --> 00:39:13,730
他说《Persona》救了他的命。
He said that Persona was the film that saved his life.

491
00:39:13,868 --> 00:39:16,561
(鼓舞人心的音乐)
[inspirational music]

492
00:39:24,500 --> 00:39:26,743
是《耻辱》还是《耻辱》?
[man] Is it Shame or The Shame?

493
00:39:26,881 --> 00:39:28,435
在瑞典语中是Skammen，
[Felicia] In Swedish it's Skammen,

494
00:39:28,573 --> 00:39:30,160
意思是"耻辱"
which means "The Shame",

495
00:39:30,298 --> 00:39:32,715
但我想英文标题是《耻辱》。
but the English title is Shame,I think.

496
00:39:32,853 --> 00:39:36,719
奇怪的是，在英国它以《耻辱》的名义发布。
Oddly enough, in the UK it was released as The Shame.

497
00:39:36,857 --> 00:39:39,894
(继续播放音乐和聊天)
[music and chatter continue]

498
00:39:48,455 --> 00:39:51,250
伯格曼知道他会受到很多批评
[Felicia] Bergman knew that he would receive a lot of criticism

499
00:39:51,389 --> 00:39:53,563
以这种方式唤起越南。
for evoking Vietnam in this manner.

500
00:39:53,701 --> 00:39:55,738
因为在瑞典关于战争的辩论
Because the debate in Sweden about the war

501
00:39:55,876 --> 00:39:57,222
非常黑和白。
was very black and white.

502
00:39:57,360 --> 00:39:59,742
他的电影非常灰暗。
His film is extremely gray.

503
00:39:59,880 --> 00:40:01,985
(音乐继续)
[music continues]

504
