00:41:20,857 --> 00:41:23,515
伯格曼可不这么看他们。
Uh, you know, Bergman didn't see them that way.

523
00:41:23,653 --> 00:41:25,655
是啊，但是，你知道的，他没有考虑
Yeah, but, you know, he didn't consider

524
00:41:25,793 --> 00:41:28,071
《透过黑暗的玻璃》，寂静与冬日之光
Through a Glass Darkly, The Silence,and Winter Light

525
00:41:28,209 --> 00:41:30,557
作为一个三部曲，然而，一些评论家仍然认为他们
as a trilogy, and yet, some critics still see them

526
00:41:30,695 --> 00:41:32,351
是关于失去信仰的三部曲。
as a trilogy about the loss of faith.

527
00:41:32,490 --> 00:41:33,870
我是说，他肯定说过这是三部曲，
I mean, he definitely said they were a trilogy,

528
00:41:34,008 --> 00:41:35,389
但后来又走了回来。
but then walked it back.

529
00:41:35,527 --> 00:41:36,701
就因为他说这是三部曲
Just because he said it's a trilogy

530
00:41:36,839 --> 00:41:38,047
并不意味着它就是1。
doesn't mean it is one.

531
00:41:38,185 --> 00:41:40,325
是的,当然。
Yeah, sure.

532
00:41:49,714 --> 00:41:51,094
谢谢你的汉普斯狩猎之旅。
Thank you for the Hampus Safari.

533
00:41:51,232 --> 00:41:52,337
希望你们喜欢。
I hope you enjoyed it.

534
00:41:52,475 --> 00:41:53,890
我很喜欢。
I loved it.

535
00:41:54,028 --> 00:41:56,272
别忘了你的羊皮。
Don't forget your sheepskins.

536
00:42:09,734 --> 00:42:11,874
你查查。再见。
-See you. -Bye.

537
00:42:19,778 --> 00:42:21,746
-嘿。——(克里斯)嘿。
-Hey. -[Chris] Hey.

538
00:42:26,613 --> 00:42:27,890
非常别致。
Très chic.

539
00:42:28,028 --> 00:42:31,238
谢谢你的支持。
Thanks for the support.

540
00:42:31,376 --> 00:42:33,620
我看到那辆巴士，吓坏了。我很抱歉。
I saw the bus and freaked out. I'm sorry.

541
00:42:33,758 --> 00:42:35,380
这是好的。
That's alright.

542
00:42:37,934 --> 00:42:39,073
它怎么样?
How was it?

543
00:42:39,211 --> 00:42:41,973
其实还不错。
It was pretty good, actually.

544
00:42:42,974 --> 00:42:44,700
是的。
Yeah.

545
00:42:44,838 --> 00:42:46,529
但我回来后一直觉得有点恶心。
But I've been feeling a bit yuck since I got back.

546
00:42:46,667 --> 00:42:49,739
-为什么,发生了什么事?-一定是汉堡的问题。
-Why, what happened? -Must have been the burger.

547
00:42:52,777 --> 00:42:54,710
你去哪了?
So, where were you?

548
00:42:55,745 --> 00:42:57,264
开车。
Driving around.

549
00:42:57,402 --> 00:42:58,610
哦,是的。开车吗?
Oh, yeah. driving around?

550
00:42:58,748 --> 00:43:00,681
嗯。我遇到了一个男人。
Mmm. I met a guy.

551
00:43:00,819 --> 00:43:02,200
哦，你遇到了一个男人?确定。
Oh, you met a guy? Sure.

552
00:43:02,338 --> 00:43:03,995
——学生。嗯。
-A student. -Hmm.

553
00:43:04,133 --> 00:43:05,755
-他是学生吗?来自斯德哥尔摩的电影专业学生。
-A student, was he? -A film student from Stockholm.

554
00:43:05,893 --> 00:43:08,482
哦。他帅吗，性感吗，还是?
Oh. Was he handsome, was he sexy, was he?

555
00:43:08,620 --> 00:43:10,173
-是的。-哦。
-Yeah. -Oh.

556
00:43:10,311 --> 00:43:12,624
当他谈到伯格曼的时候，他是不是很聪明?
Was he brilliant when he talked about Bergman?

557
00:43:12,762 --> 00:43:15,316
虽然不像你，但他的笨拙很有魅力。
Not like you, but, um, his clumsiness had its charm.

558
00:43:15,454 --> 00:43:18,526
哦,谢谢。闭嘴。
Oh, thanks. Shut up.

559
00:43:29,641 --> 00:43:31,091
(打印机转动)
[printer whirring]

560
00:43:38,788 --> 00:43:41,480
(时钟的滴答声)
[clock ticking]

561
00:43:52,940 --> 00:43:54,390
(定时停止)
[ticking stops]

562
00:44:06,954 --> 00:44:08,991
【脚步声】
[footsteps approaching]

563
00:45:23,272 --> 00:45:25,930
在找什么东西吗?
Looking for something, huh?

564
00:45:27,379 --> 00:45:29,554
-不。-哦。
-No. -Oh.

565
00:45:37,458 --> 00:45:39,426
(Chris嘎嘎叫)
[Chris quacking]

566
00:46:14,841 --> 00:46:17,119
(温柔的音乐)
[gentle music]

567
00:47:02,785 --> 00:47:05,063
(遥远的聊天)
[distant chatter]

568
00:47:11,967 --> 00:47:14,176
(音乐继续)
[music continues]

569
00:47:15,625 --> 00:47:17,248
嘿。嗨。
Hey. Hi.

570
00:47:17,386 --> 00:47:18,525
我正在找房子
I'm looking for the house

571
00:47:18,663 --> 00:47:20,907
《透过黑暗的玻璃》。
from Through a Glass Darkly.

572
00:47:21,045 --> 00:47:23,150
伯格曼的电影。
Bergman's film.

573
00:47:24,980 --> 00:47:27,051
对不起，我不懂英语。
Sorry, don't understand English.

574
00:47:27,189 --> 00:47:29,847
英格玛·伯格曼吗?
Ingmar Bergman?

575
00:47:31,227 --> 00:47:33,264
那个住在岛上的电影制作人。
The filmmaker who lived on the island.

576
00:47:33,402 --> 00:47:35,197
对不起。
Sorry.

577
00:47:36,819 --> 00:47:38,372
(继续喋喋不休)
[chatter continues]

578
00:47:39,546 --> 00:47:40,581
(瑞典)
[in Swedish]

579
00:47:45,759 --> 00:47:47,209
[克里斯]哦，别这样。
[Chris] Oh, come on.

580
00:47:51,109 --> 00:47:53,422
(雷声隆隆地)
[thunder rumbles]

581
00:47:53,560 --> 00:47:55,527
(大雨)
[rain pouring]

582
00:48:01,016 --> 00:48:03,259
(雷声崩溃)
[thunder crashing]

583
00:48:26,834 --> 00:48:29,837
-(走近的脚步声)-你想一起吃午饭吗?
-[footsteps approaching] -You want to have lunch?

584
00:48:33,048 --> 00:48:34,773
呵。——(叹息)
-Yikes. -[sighs]

585
00:48:39,951 --> 00:48:43,127
我从《透过黑暗的玻璃》看房子，
I went to see the house from Through a Glass Darkly,

586
00:48:43,265 --> 00:48:44,645
但是我找不到。
but I couldn't find it.

587
00:48:44,783 --> 00:48:47,096
——不是。从来没有。-什么?
-There isn't one. Never was. -What?

588
00:48:47,234 --> 00:48:49,064
但是地图上的图片呢?
But the picture on the map?

589
00:48:49,202 --> 00:48:51,514
他们建造了立面，然后在工作室里拍摄了内部。
They built the facade, and they shot the interiors in a studio.

590
00:48:52,791 --> 00:48:54,414
伯格曼Safari,宝贝。
Bergman Safari, babes.

591
00:48:57,417 --> 00:48:59,315
(托尼)最近怎么样?你在哪里?
[Tony] How's it going? Where you at?

592
00:48:59,453 --> 00:49:01,145
(叹气)我还在写大纲，
[sighs] I'm still doing the outline,

593
00:49:01,283 --> 00:49:03,664
但我不知道我是否想写。
but I don't know if I want to write it.

594
00:49:03,802 --> 00:49:05,839
为什么不呢?
Why not?

595
00:49:05,977 --> 00:49:08,359
因为我怕这是我已经做过的事。
Because I'm afraid it's like stuff I've already done.

596
00:49:08,497 --> 00:49:11,810
不…不可能的。
No... not possible.

597
00:49:11,949 --> 00:49:12,950
我以为我们花了一辈子
I thought we spent all whole lives

598
00:49:13,088 --> 00:49:14,813
说着同样的话。
saying the same thing.

599
00:49:14,952 --> 00:49:17,678
是的，但角度不同。
We do, but from different perspectives.

600
00:49:17,816 --> 00:49:19,991
你只需要相信你自己。
You just gotta trust yourself.

601
00:49:24,823 --> 00:49:29,311
人物，对话，场景，一切都很契合，
Characters, the dialogues, the situations, it all fits,

602
00:49:29,449 --> 00:49:31,865
但有些东西在阻止我。
but something is holding me back.

603
00:49:32,003 --> 00:49:33,418
有些事让我很焦虑。
Something is making me anxious.

604
00:49:33,556 --> 00:49:35,075
那就不一样了。
Oh, well, that's different.

605
00:49:35,213 --> 00:49:38,389
如果这让你感到焦虑，那就休息一下。
If it's making you anxious, take a break.

606
00:49:38,527 --> 00:49:40,874
你刚说了"写"。现在你说“不要写”。
You just said "write". Now you say "don't write".

607
00:49:41,012 --> 00:49:42,841
这没有帮助。这并不容易!
That doesn't help. It's not easy!

608
00:49:42,980 --> 00:49:44,326
你知道写作对我来说有多难。
You know how hard writing is for me.

609
00:49:44,464 --> 00:49:45,568
它是折磨。
It's--it's torture.

610
00:49:45,706 --> 00:49:47,053
这是自己造成的痛苦。
It's self-inflicted agony.

611
00:49:47,191 --> 00:49:48,606
这是石头上流出的血。
It's blood from a stone.

612
00:49:48,744 --> 00:49:53,266
好吧，那就干点别的吧!
Well, then, do something else!

613
00:49:53,404 --> 00:49:55,613
是吗，全职家庭主妇?
Yeah, like what, full-time housewife?

614
00:49:55,751 --> 00:49:57,684
这是一个光荣的职业。
Well, it's an honorable profession.

615
00:50:03,517 --> 00:50:06,762
你知道，写作对你来说没必要这么困难。
You know, there's no reason writing has to be so difficult for you.

616
00:50:06,900 --> 00:50:08,729
你不是15。你已长大。
You're not 15. You've outgrown that.

617
00:50:08,867 --> 00:50:11,594
也许我是，因为我没有。
Well, maybe I am because I haven't.

618
00:50:14,908 --> 00:50:16,392
写别的东西。
Write something else.

619
00:50:16,530 --> 00:50:17,738
我又不是有一堆项目要做
It's not like I have a ton of projects

620
00:50:17,876 --> 00:50:19,533
在我的脑海里排成一行。
lined up in my head.

621
00:50:21,535 --> 00:50:23,675
我真的以为你会鼓励我。
I really thought you would encourage me.

622
00:50:23,813 --> 00:50:25,022
我尝试。
I'm trying.

623
00:50:26,609 --> 00:50:28,922
你知道我喜欢你的作品。
You know I love your work.

624
00:50:32,270 --> 00:50:34,410
你的事情怎么样了?
How's your thing going?

625
00:50:34,548 --> 00:50:36,792
事实上，还不错。
Um, pretty good, actually.

626
00:50:38,069 --> 00:50:39,450
它是什么?
What's it about?

627
00:50:39,588 --> 00:50:41,279
这是,嗯,
It's about, um,

628
00:50:41,417 --> 00:50:45,145
看不见的东西是如何循环的
how invisible things circulate

629
00:50:45,283 --> 00:50:47,182
在几。
within a couple.

630
00:50:48,769 --> 00:50:50,392
和这个故事吗?
And the story?

631
00:50:53,429 --> 00:50:55,811
你怎么什么都不告诉我?我什么都告诉你。
Why don't you ever tell me anything? I tell you everything.

632
00:50:55,949 --> 00:50:57,951
-我可不想扫你的兴。-哦。
-Don't wanna jinx it. -Oh.

633
00:51:00,367 --> 00:51:02,059
你能告诉我它发生在哪里吗?
Can you tell me where it takes place?

634
00:51:02,197 --> 00:51:03,267
在这里。
Here.

635
00:51:03,405 --> 00:51:05,338
在这儿?法吗?-是的。
-Here?! Faro? -Yeah.

636
00:51:05,476 --> 00:51:07,271
别说得好像我应该知道似的。
Don't say that like I'm supposed to know.

637
00:51:07,409 --> 00:51:08,755
-嗯，我以为你说了。-不,我没有,
-Well, I thought you did. -No, I don't,

638
00:51:08,893 --> 00:51:10,757
因为你什么都不告诉我。
because you don't tell me anything.

639
00:51:17,936 --> 00:51:19,973
-[托尼]我有头衔了。-嗯。
-[Tony] I've got a title. -Mmm.

640
00:51:20,111 --> 00:51:22,734
你可以保守秘密。
You can keep it to yourself.

641
00:51:23,632 --> 00:51:25,910
(雨声)
[rain pattering]

642
00:51:48,691 --> 00:51:50,797
有什么事吗?
What's the matter?

643
00:51:57,252 --> 00:51:59,116
是你的剧本吗?
Is it your script?

644
00:52:10,334 --> 00:52:12,198
琼小姐，你想回家吗?
Miss June, you want to go home?

645
00:52:12,336 --> 00:52:14,269
你确定吗?
You sure?

646
00:52:18,169 --> 00:52:20,067
(悄悄哭泣)
[sobs quietly]

647
00:52:23,554 --> 00:52:25,659
(鸟唱歌)
[birds singing]

648
00:52:34,461 --> 00:52:36,498
(写在纸上)
[writing on paper]

649
00:53:12,361 --> 00:53:14,777
我能告诉你我在写什么吗?
Can I tell you about what I'm writing?

650
00:53:14,915 --> 00:53:16,779
是的。
Yeah.

651
00:53:18,367 --> 00:53:20,921
这是一个更长的故事的最后一集。
It's the last episode of a longer story.

652
00:53:21,059 --> 00:53:23,545
所以，也许它太脆弱了，不够拍电影，
So, maybe it's too flimsy and not enough for a movie,

653
00:53:23,683 --> 00:53:26,272
-但我想听听你的意见。-好的。
-but I would like your opinion. -Okay.

654
00:53:26,410 --> 00:53:28,929
所以它发生了
So it takes place

655
00:53:29,067 --> 00:53:32,278
在婚礼上呆了三天
over three days at a wedding.

656
00:53:33,796 --> 00:53:35,281
我还不知道在哪里
I don't know where yet,

657
00:53:35,419 --> 00:53:39,077
但也许像这样的地方。
but maybe a place like here.

658
00:53:39,216 --> 00:53:40,838
像法。
Like Faro.

659
00:53:40,976 --> 00:53:43,910
一个岛屿，实际上会很好。
An island, actually, would work very well.

660
00:53:44,048 --> 00:53:47,327
可以从飞机上开始。
Um, and it could start on the plane.

661
00:53:47,465 --> 00:53:49,709
或者在船上。
Or maybe on a boat.

662
00:53:49,847 --> 00:53:51,642
(神奇的音乐)
[magical music]

663
00:53:51,780 --> 00:53:53,609
[克里斯]我们在波罗的海的渡船上，
[Chris] So, we're on a ferry in the Baltic Sea,

664
00:53:53,747 --> 00:53:55,784
从大陆到哥特兰
from the mainland to Gotland.

665
00:53:55,922 --> 00:53:58,925
要四个小时的车程，而且现在是春天。
It's a four-hour ride, and it's spring.

666
00:53:59,063 --> 00:54:01,652
或许应该是夏天。
Or maybe it should be summer.

667
00:54:01,790 --> 00:54:03,309
这是夏末。
It's late summer.

668
00:54:03,447 --> 00:54:05,000
(聊天)
[chatter]

669
00:54:05,138 --> 00:54:06,933
一个年轻的女人望着远方。
A young woman looks into the distance.

670
00:54:07,071 --> 00:54:09,176
她的名字叫艾米。
Her name is Amy.

671
00:54:09,315 --> 00:54:12,766
她和我差不多大，或者比我小一点。
She's about my age or maybe a bit younger.

672
00:54:12,904 --> 00:54:15,631
假设她28岁。
Let's say she's 28.

673
00:54:15,769 --> 00:54:19,186
(音乐继续)
[music continues]

674
00:54:19,325 --> 00:54:23,501
她是这部电影的主角。
She's the main character of the film.

675
00:54:23,639 --> 00:54:26,297
她那天早上从纽约到达了斯德哥尔摩。
She arrived in Stockholm that morning from New York.

676
00:54:26,435 --> 00:54:28,541
她是来参加老朋友妮珂莱特的婚礼的，
She's come for the wedding of an old friend, Nicolette,

677
00:54:28,679 --> 00:54:33,200
她要嫁给一个叫乔纳斯的瑞典人
who's marrying a Swede named Jonas.

678
00:54:33,339 --> 00:54:34,995
庆祝活动在一个岛上举行
The celebration takes place on an island

679
00:54:35,133 --> 00:54:37,135
在哥特兰的北端。
off the northern tip of Gotland.

680
00:54:37,274 --> 00:54:39,379
一个叫法罗的岛。
An island called Faro.

681
00:54:39,517 --> 00:54:41,899
这对艾米来说并非无关紧要
Which is hardly insignificant to Amy,

682
00:54:42,037 --> 00:54:44,315
-因为她是导演。-好的。
-as she's a director. -Alright.

683
00:54:44,453 --> 00:54:47,870
伯格曼在她的想象中占据了非常重要的位置。
And Bergman occupies a very important place in her imagination.

684
00:54:48,008 --> 00:54:50,735
对很多人来说，他是令人敬畏的推荐人，
For many, he's a formidable reference,

685
00:54:50,873 --> 00:54:53,013
但对她来说，他是……
but for her, he is...

686
00:54:53,151 --> 00:54:55,913
一种避难所，一种安慰。
sort of refuge, a consolation.

687
00:54:56,051 --> 00:54:58,364
-嗯。——然而……
-Mm-hmm. -And yet...

688
00:54:58,502 --> 00:55:01,401
但她现在想的不是他。
and yet it's not him she's thinking about right now.

689
00:55:01,539 --> 00:55:04,335
另一个男人占据了她的思想。
Another man is monopolizing her thoughts.

690
00:55:04,473 --> 00:55:06,924
他的名字叫约瑟夫。
Joseph is his name.

691
00:55:07,062 --> 00:55:09,409
约瑟夫，她不能放手。
Joseph she can't let go.

692
00:55:09,547 --> 00:55:13,931
艾米15岁的时候遇到了17岁的约瑟夫。
Amy was 15 when she met Joseph, who was 17.

693
00:55:14,069 --> 00:55:19,039
他们像青少年一样热烈而笨拙地爱着对方。
They loved each other passionately and awkwardly, like teenagers do.

694
00:55:19,177 --> 00:55:21,525
他们把对方撕成碎片。
And they tore each other to pieces.

695
00:55:21,663 --> 00:55:25,218
约瑟夫在艾米18岁那天离开了她。
Joseph left Amy the day she turned 18.

696
00:55:26,806 --> 00:55:28,359
他们各走各的路，
They each went their own ways,

697
00:55:28,497 --> 00:55:30,603
但艾米从未忘记约瑟夫。
but Amy never forgot Joseph.

698
00:55:30,741 --> 00:55:33,191
当他们多年后再次见面时，
When they saw each other again years later,

699
00:55:33,330 --> 00:55:36,056
他们意识到他们的感情还在。
they realized that their feelings were still there.

